  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dda \u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister prepares for a big change in the port",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ports, Shipping and Aviation Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said that modern facilities will be created at the passenger terminal of Colombo Port for foreign tourists coming to Sri Lanka by air as well as ships.",
        "The Minister said this after observing the condition of the passenger terminal premises of Colombo Port yesterday (18) morning.",
        "The minister said that he had discussed with all the shipping companies and representatives of Sri Lanka to bring the passenger ships to Sri Lanka and mentioned that the business promotion division of the port should implement a large number of publicity programs for this purpose on the Internet.",
        "Tourist passenger ships have visited the port of Colombo in large numbers in recent times. But due to the covid epidemic situation and the economic instability in the country in recent days, the arrival of passenger ships has stopped. But aiming at the upcoming tourist season, the premises including the passenger terminal should be equipped with modern facilities in such a way as to attract the tourists. Arrangements should be made to provide an air-conditioned parking hall with modern facilities, sanitary facilities, an attractive duty-free shopping mall, and transport facilities.",
        "The minister mentioned that he is committed to contribute to the port's contribution to the foreign exchange acquisition program initiated by the government as the minister in charge of the subject."
      ],
